00:25:34.230 --> 00:25:39.865
but the real point is that
Newton and Galileo did not

00:25:39.865 --> 00:25:43.159
know anything about relative
effects like time dilation.

00:25:43.159 --> 00:25:45.325
So for them, it was just
obvious that all clocks ran

00:25:45.325 --> 00:25:48.350
at the same speed,
and time was naturally

00:25:48.350 --> 00:25:51.319
universal-- naturally absolute.

00:25:51.319 --> 00:25:52.860
In this case, we're
aware of the fact

00:25:52.860 --> 00:25:55.300
that moving clocks run
at different speeds.

00:25:55.300 --> 00:25:58.705
So if we were to take
these clocks between us

00:25:58.705 --> 00:26:00.930
and the galaxy, and
transport one to the other,

00:26:00.930 --> 00:26:03.500
depending on what path we
used to transport them on,

00:26:03.500 --> 00:26:06.650
in the end, they would probably
not agree with each other.

00:26:06.650 --> 00:26:09.334
So, we're setting
up a definition

00:26:09.334 --> 00:26:13.860
of what we're going to define
locally as time, recognizing

00:26:13.860 --> 00:26:17.770
that what time means here,
versus what time means there,

00:26:17.770 --> 00:26:20.260
is a consequence of our
assumptions about how we define

00:26:20.260 --> 00:26:20.760
things.

00:26:20.760 --> 00:26:22.800
It is not given
automatically by the fact

00:26:22.800 --> 00:26:24.686
that all clocks will
run at the same speed.

